          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688741116779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688741116779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688741116779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When everything's nearly ready, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add your<strong> ground paprika </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>mix everything together</p><p>Add your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> to the pan with the the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 3-4 min on each side – this is your <strong>buttery paprika basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688741113152-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688741113152-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
